word_mean_info__list.difference: 较正式用词，侧重已经开始，且希望完成，但常隐含着不一定有预期的结果。
和endeavour一样，表示付出巨大努力，但strive侧重劳累与紧张，而不强调努力的结果。
正式用词，指尽最大努力、认真地克服困难去做某事。
普通用词，可与attempt换用，但强调努力或尝试，后跟不定式表示努力或争取；后跟动名词表示尝试。

这是他第三十一次尝试。

list.abstract: attempt（英 [əˈtempt]，美 [əˈtempt]），英语单词，作动词为试图做；试图登上；企图夺取。作名词为尝试；努力；企图杀害。短语搭配有attempt to（企图；尝试；试图）、attempt to do（企图做；尝试做）等。例句：Very Serious People's attempt to cripple the economy.（人们想要破坏经济的企图非常严重。） attempt的近义词有essay、attack、push等。

yingyinNormal.en: That was a joke, or an attempt at one. Next question.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那只是个笑话，或许是曾经有过的尝试，下一个问题。

yingyinNormal.en: We're going to attempt a manned mission. NASA said it would take five years.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们准备尝试载人航天计划，航空航天局预计要花五年时间。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm going to attempt an experiment that will get you to transfer those feelings to me.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我准备尝试一个实验让你将这些情感转移到我身上。

yingyinNormal.en: Why didn't you attempt to return to LaGuardia? There simply was not enough altitude.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你为什么不尝试返回拉瓜迪亚机场？显然没有足够的高度。

yingyinNormal.en: And? And that means each iteration is an attempt to prove its own proof. It's recursive. It's nonsensical.
yingyinNormal.zh: 所以呢？这表示每一个迭代都只是在尝试自我证明，这是递归，是没有意义的。

yingyinNormal.en: The Hudson was the only place that was long enough and smooth enough and wide enough to even attempt to land the airplane safely.
yingyinNormal.zh: 只有哈德逊河足够长，足够平和足够宽，来冒险尝试把飞机安全降落。

yingyinNormal.en: Answer yes or no. Has there ever been, against my express instructions, any attempt at a psychiatric evaluation of Eurus Holmes?
yingyinNormal.zh: 回答是或不是，你们是否曾违反我的明确指令尝试对欧罗斯·福尔摩斯进行过精神鉴定。

yingyinNormal.en: If America Works succeeds, we will reinvent the American dream. If we fail in our attempt, we will admit it frankly and try another.
yingyinNormal.zh: 如果美国就业法案成功了，我们将彻底改造美国梦，如果我们的尝试失败，我们会坦白承认，然后重新来过。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, I will share with you the facts and evidence as they were available to me, and in this very room, you will all attempt to solve the case of Blessington The Poisoner.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我将告诉大家当时我已知的事实和证据，就在这里，大家可以尝试解开下毒者布莱辛顿之谜。

yingyinNormal.en: So, why attempt the impossible? Why follow your dream?
yingyinNormal.zh: 那为何要挑战不可能？为何要追寻梦想？

yingyinNormal.en: Any attempt on the director's life had to look successful.
yingyinNormal.zh: 为了让人觉得局长真的被谋杀了。

yingyinNormal.en: Mother and Father were terrified. They thought it was a suicide attempt.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们的父母吓坏了。以为她是想自杀。

yingyinNormal.en: I'll attempt to access everyone in his inner circle. You stay on the number.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我要黑进他核心集团的每一个人，你盯紧号码。

yingyinNormal.en: I'm just sorry I'm not gonna be around to watch you two attempt to handle this.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真遗憾不能留下来看你照顾孩子手忙脚乱了。

yingyinNormal.en: Your unwillingness to accept empirical evidence suggests an attempt at flattery.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你不愿接受经验实据，说明一种奉承之举。

yingyinNormal.en: Nothing. It was a desperate attempt to introduce an alternate topic of conversation.
yingyinNormal.zh: 没关联，我只是迫切想为午餐会换个新话题罢了。

yingyinNormal.en: There was an assassination attempt in the fortress. Some tragedies were averted, some were not.
yingyinNormal.zh: 确实有人曾试图在宫中行刺，有些悲剧得以避免，有的没有。

yingyinNormal.en: Footage of the assassination attempt is still making its way to us, and we expect to have that shortly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 刺杀未遂事件的视频还没送到，但相信很快能够公布。

yingyinNormal.en: Now, Mr. Gardner will attempt to explain away this DNA in many exotic ways and in fact, like any good defense attorney.
yingyinNormal.zh: 加德纳先生会试着用许多特别的方法来为DNA辩解，实际上与任何优秀的辩护律师一样。

yingyinNormal.en: Philippe. My sons are consummate wire walkers. And I would never allow them to attempt such a walk without safety line.
yingyinNormal.zh: 菲利浦，我儿子都是高明的走钢索人，我绝不准他们不用安全索就上路。

direction_info.description:
数据源自2012-2023年12年间全国考研试卷，由搜狗翻译进行大数据分析汇总，数据仅供参考。

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>
由搜狗翻译收集历年真题试卷、汇总单词出现的总频次、释义分布。题型选自2012-2023年全国考研英语一和考研英语二共24套考研试卷，包括阅读、完型填空、翻译、写作等所有题型。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>
精选2012-2023年12年间全国考研英语一和考研英语二试卷，由搜狗大数据与搜索内容匹配历年真题例句。

搜狗翻译拥有最终解释权。

sense_info_list.en: an act of trying to achieve something, typically one that is unsuccessful or not certain to succeed

examination_example.sentence: This is why repeated <highlight>attempts</highlight> at reform legislation have failed in recent years.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这就是为什么近年来改革立法的多次尝试都失败了。

examination_example.sentence: A recent study <highlight>attempts</highlight> to separate them by looking at bribery prosecutions under America's Foreign Corrupt Practices Act (FCPA).
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最近的一项研究试图区分它们，通过研究因违反《美国反海外腐败法》而遭到行贿起诉的案例。

examination_example.sentence: Arizona had <highlight>attempted</highlight> to fashion state policies that ran parallel to the existing federal ones.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 亚利桑那州曾尝试制定与现有联邦政策平行的州政策。

word_usage.usage: attempt作名词时，其后可接to do sth.或者at doing sth.，表示“做……的企图，尝试”，如：an attempt to cut costs 削减成本的尝试。
attempt作动词时，既可作及物动词，其后接名词或者代词，如：attempt an escape，又可作不及物动词，通常接to do的形式，如：attempt to answer all your questions 试着回答你所有的问题。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 较正式，意为“试图、设法作一番努力”，后常与to连用。
常用词，意为“试图、尽力、设法”。
正式用语，意为“努力，尽力(后接to)”，指为达到目标而做的一切努力。

examination_example.sentence: Silence may be viewed by some cultural groups as extremely uncomfortable; therefore <highlight>attempts</highlight> may be made to fill every gap (间隙) with conversation.
